parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to a higher risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbag may not deploy properly or may explode and send shrapnel into the vehicle's occupants.
symptoms: None
as this issue is related to the recall repair process rather than a specific vehicle malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy
ABS and ESC warning lights flickering
brake pedal and accelerator pedal failure to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in repairing the vehicle, leaving the driver and occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None
as this issue is related to the recall repair process rather than a specific vehicle malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or suddenly shift into neutral, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into neutral while driving
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the transmission makes a clunking sound
the gear indicator flashes
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the transmission kicks down to a lower gear when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering and brake systems can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fails
the brakes fail
the airbag light illuminates
the fuel system leaks
the engine overheats
the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The wiring harness of the temperature sensor fails
the connector wires are insufficiently crimped
the clutch opens
the vehicle shifts into neutral
the selector lever position indicator flashes
the depress brake pedal indicator light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause loss of power, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The engine speed ball drops
the engine overheats
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS and ESC warning lights are illuminated
the brakes lock up
the vehicle is difficult to control
the brakes are unresponsive
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.
